weltengreif / 03.01.2017 / gefundenIn order to use up my remaining vacation days and to make the most of the weather (huh?) I decided to go to Nuremberg for two days. On the one hand, I had a few D5s ripe for the picking over here, and on the other, more significant hand, I had recently logged Deutschlandtour cache no. 16, and I was eager to finalise the series. This time the overnight train ride left me quite a bit more shattered than usual, but luckily that was nothing a walk through the brisk winter air and a D5/T5 couldn't mend. With one notable exception all my must-have smilies were collected, and apart from the necessarily cumbersome backpack I ran into no significant trouble. The cold got to me at times, but as long as I had some stamina left I was usually able to get myself cosily warm after a while. Cachewise there was little in the way of either quality or quantity, but the statistics were boosted a little, and my solved mysteries DB got a little smaller. Thanks to all COs putting in the (wo)man- and brainpower!Quick take on a 2.5h stopover in FFM.TFTC!Cache # (approx.)Found on 3. Januar 2017 at 03:34
